{"title_page": "Jean-Guy Allard", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date  = 1948\n| birth_place = [[Shawinigan]], [[Quebec]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and given age|2016|08|16|68}}\n| death_place = [[Havana]], Cuba \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| occupation  = Journalist \n| known_for   = \n}}\n\n'''Jean-Guy Allard''' (1948 \u2013 August 16, 2016) was a Canadian journalist, who worked as an editor and reporter for ''[[Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al]]'' and ''[[Le Journal de Qu\u00e9bec]]'' from 1971 to 2000.<ref name=agresion>Jean-Guy Allard and Eva Golinger (2009), [https://web.archive.org/web/20120922142408/http://www.centrodealerta.org/documentos_desclasificados/libro_completo_la_agresion_.pdf La Agresi\u00f3n Permanente: USAID, NED y CIA], Caracas: Ministerio del Poder Poder Popular para la Comunicaci\u00f3n y la Informaci\u00f3n, p5 (archived)</ref> He retired to [[Cuba]], and later wrote for ''[[Granma (newspaper)|Granma]]''.<ref name=agresion/> He wrote several books, including one on [[Robert M\u00e9nard]] and ''[[Reporters without Borders]]'', and one on [[Luis Posada Carriles]].<ref name=agresion/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telesurtv.net/english/opinion/Jean-Guy-Allard-Model-for-Journalists-in-the-Capitalist-System-20160818-0041.html|title=Jean-Guy Allard: Model for Journalists in the Capitalist System|work=telesurtv.net|accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* (with Marie-Dominique Bertuccioli), ''Le dossier Robert M\u00e9nard: pourquoi Reporters sans fronti\u00e8res (RSF) s'acharne sur Cuba'', Montreal/Paris: Lanct\u00f4t \u00e9diteur, 2004\n* ''La fili\u00e8re terroriste du FBI'', Tim\u00e9li (Ginebra), 2005\n* ''Posada Carriles, cuarenta a\u00f1os de terror'', Editora Politica (La Habana), 2006\n* ''Washington - Miami: la conexi\u00f3n terrorista del FBI'', Editora Politica (La Habana), 2008\n* (with [[Eva Golinger]]), ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20120303163938/http://www.centrodealerta.org/noticias/nuevo_libro_la_agresion_per.html La Agresi\u00f3n Permanente: USAID, NED y CIA]'', Caracas: Ministerio del Poder Poder Popular para la Comunicaci\u00f3n y la Informaci\u00f3n, 2009 (Review in Spanish)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Allard, Jean-Guy}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Journalists from Quebec]]\n[[Category:People from Shawinigan]]\n[[Category:Writers from Quebec]]\n\n\n{{Canada-journalist-stub}}\n{{Quebec-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date  = 1948\n| birth_place = [[Shawinigan]], [[Quebec]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and given age|2016|08|16|68}}\n| death_place = [[Havana]], Cuba \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| occupation  = Journalist \n| known_for   = \n}}\n\n'''Jean-Guy Allard''' (1948 \u2013 August 16, 2016) was a Canadian journalist, who worked as an editor and reporter for ''[[Le Journal de Montr\u00e9al]]'' and ''[[Le Journal de Qu\u00e9bec]]'' from 1971 to 2000.<ref name=agresion>Jean-Guy Allard and Eva Golinger (2009), [http://www.centrodealerta.org/documentos_desclasificados/libro_completo_la_agresion_.pdf La Agresi\u00f3n Permanente: USAID, NED y CIA], Caracas: Ministerio del Poder Poder Popular para la Comunicaci\u00f3n y la Informaci\u00f3n, p5</ref> He retired to [[Cuba]], and later wrote for ''[[Granma (newspaper)|Granma]]''.<ref name=agresion/> He wrote several books, including one on [[Robert M\u00e9nard]] and ''[[Reporters without Borders]]'', and one on [[Luis Posada Carriles]].<ref name=agresion/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telesurtv.net/english/opinion/Jean-Guy-Allard-Model-for-Journalists-in-the-Capitalist-System-20160818-0041.html|title=Jean-Guy Allard: Model for Journalists in the Capitalist System|work=telesurtv.net|accessdate=21 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* (with Marie-Dominique Bertuccioli), ''Le dossier Robert M\u00e9nard: pourquoi Reporters sans fronti\u00e8res (RSF) s'acharne sur Cuba'', Montreal/Paris: Lanct\u00f4t \u00e9diteur, 2004\n* ''La fili\u00e8re terroriste du FBI'', Tim\u00e9li (Ginebra), 2005\n* ''Posada Carriles, cuarenta a\u00f1os de terror'', Editora Politica (La Habana), 2006\n* ''Washington - Miami: la conexi\u00f3n terrorista del FBI'', Editora Politica (La Habana), 2008\n* (with [[Eva Golinger]]), ''[http://www.centrodealerta.org/noticias/nuevo_libro_la_agresion_per.html La Agresi\u00f3n Permanente: USAID, NED y CIA]'', Caracas: Ministerio del Poder Poder Popular para la Comunicaci\u00f3n y la Informaci\u00f3n, 2009\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Allard, Jean-Guy}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:2016 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Journalists from Quebec]]\n[[Category:People from Shawinigan]]\n[[Category:Writers from Quebec]]\n\n\n{{Canada-journalist-stub}}\n{{Quebec-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Objectivesea", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed two dead links with data from archive.org", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Guy_Allard"}
